  "body": "Currently, it is not possible to define methods on a Class inheriting from a `React.createClass` component constructor, without having any colliding methods [automatically replaced](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/d7b59de1c39c509aaf0d9d3f16999dc14fc5bd14/src/isomorphic/classic/class/ReactClass.js#L816-L818) by the methods which have been designated for autobinding.\n\nThis adds a simple check to ensure the function in the `__reactAutoBindMap` is === to the method on the component it intends to replace, otherwise the auto-binding does not replace the method on the inheriting class body.\n\nTo visualize, adapted from the included test:\n\n``` js\nvar ParentComponent = React.createClass({\n  testMethod: function() {\n    throw new Error();\n  },\n  componentDidMount: function() {\n    this.testMethod();\n  },\n  render: function() {\n    return <div />;\n  },\n});\n\nclass ChildComponent extends ParentComponent {\n  testMethod() {\n  }\n}\n```\n\nPreviously, `testMethod` on the ParentComponent always replaces that of the `ChildComponent`, and `Error` would always be thrown.\n",
